#30000
The Gates of Gadrizal~
You emerge from a mass of twisted brambles and other unpleasant
vegetation to find yourself in a rough clearing, facing a set of massive
gates crudely carved from granite.  Walls of rough-hewn stone stretch east
and west for some distance.  You can distantly see well-armed sentries
patrolling the walls, and the gatehouse seems particularly well-manned.  A
heavy wooden bridge surrounds a wide moat filled with deep, murky water. 
Wagons and travellers drift in and out of city, and the sound of the
gutteral trollish tongue reaches your ears.  You may enter the city to the
north.  
~
