#30011
The Grand Temple Square~
This huge square is a wonder to behold.  The obsidian ground is perfectly
smooth, and carved into are beautiful scenes depicting both great battles
and surreal nature scenes.  Exquisite statues of both flora and fauna are
carved straight from the ground, giving them the appearance of life being
brought forth by the cold earth.  There are ample carved stone seats and
benches, so people can sit here and contemplate the beauty of the
sculptures.  Strategically placed lights glow softly, highlight both the
details and the shadows.  The temple of Selina looms to the north, its
presence both fascinating and foreboding.  Subsidary buildings of the temple
complex lie to the east and west.  
